<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Current Election Results Show Kravchuk Leading Kuchma </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Current Election Results Show Kravchuk Leading Kuchma </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Kravchuk Leads by 2 Million Votes </H4>

<F P=102> LD2806090194 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 0800 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2806090194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Ukrainian Central Electoral Commission is still 
counting the results of the elections held on Sunday [26 June]. 
However, officials in Kiev are by now convinced that Leonid 
Kravchuk is in the lead in the vote count. INTERFAX has learned 
this from the head of the Ukrainian president's information 
service, Vladimir Shlyaposhnikov. 
  Unofficial data for 1000 today, as received by INTERFAX, 
show 
that the gap between the present head of state and his main 
rival in the elections, Leonid Kuchma, is about two million 
votes. The situation is as yet unclear only in Donetsk and 
Ivano-Frankovsk oblasts. 

</TEXT>

