<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Upper House Okays Peacekeeping Force for Georgia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Upper House Okays Peacekeeping Force for Georgia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2706133794 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 25 Jun 94 
First Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM2706133794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Russian Federation Federal Assembly Federation Council </F>
Decree No. 136-I SF, signed by Shumeyko and dated 21 June 1994: 
"On the Use of Russian Federation Armed Forces To Carry Out a 
Peacekeeping Operation in the Georgian-Abkhaz Conflict Zone"] 
  [Text] Having examined the Russian Federation president's 
appeal No. Pr-714 of 9 June 1994, and given the repeated 
requests from E. Shevardnadze, Georgian head of state, and V. 
Ardzinba, chairman of the Abkhaz Supreme Council, the Federation 
Council decrees, in accordance with Article 102 Part 1 Paragraph 
"c" of the Russian Federation Constitution, that: 
  1. The use be permitted of a contingent of up to 3,000 men 
from the Russian Federation Armed Forces with an initial mandate 
of six months to carry out a peacekeeping operation in the 
Georgian-Abkhaz conflict zone on a voluntary basis. 
  2. The Federation Council Committee for Security and Defense 
Issues, the Federation Council Committee for CIS Affairs, and 
the Federation Council Committee for International Affairs be 
instructed to monitor the implementation of this decree. 
  3. This decree comes into force from the moment it is 
adopted. 
  [Signed] V.F. Shumeyko, chairman of the Russian Federation 
Federal Assembly Federation Council 
  [Dated] Moscow, 21 June 1994 
  No. 136-I SF 

</TEXT>

