<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Committee Says Agricultural Situation `Catastrophic' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Committee Says Agricultural Situation `Catastrophic' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806094094 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 0800 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2806094094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Federation Council committee for agrarian policy 
has described the situation in the Russian agro-industrial 
complex in 1994 as extreme and catastrophic. In its statement 
it forecasts a production slump in agricultural enterprises of 
all types of ownership in 1994. It suggests that compared to 
average annual figures for 1986-90, production will fall by 
between 45 and 50 percent. The committee believes that in those 
conditions emergency economic measures are needed to support the 
agricultural sector. 

</TEXT>

