<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chubays Supports Duma Demands on Privatization </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chubays Supports Duma Demands on Privatization </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406224694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1419 
GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2406224694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 24 June -- Anatoliy Chubays has reacted very 
quickly to deputies' demands in the State Duma today to create a 
solid legal basis for the privatization process. The chairman 
of the state committee for the management of state property sent 
a telegram which was circulated as quickly among the deputies 
during the plenary session. 
  "Taking into consideration the wishes of the deputies and on 
the basis of the presidential resolution of 10 June 1994, I 
think it would be expedient for the government to submit for the 
State Duma's consideration the bill "On the state program of 
privatization of state and municipal enterprises," Anatoliy 
Chubays wrote. He told the parliamentarians that the state 
committee for the management of state property had already 
prepared such a bill and it could be submitted to the State Duma 
immediately after Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin's return 
from his foreign business trip on 25 June. 

</TEXT>

