<H3> <TI>   FCS Group To Relocate Near U.S. Compound </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    FCS Group To Relocate Near U.S. Compound </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK2806115094 Moscow KURANTY in Russian 28 Jun 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> MK2806115094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KURANTY </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Nikolay Popov report: "The Federal Counterintelligence </F>
Service Changes Premises"] 
  [Text] As your correspondent has learned from an informed 
source, the nation's pride -- the Federal Counterintelligence 
Service [FCS] -- is changing its "haunts." Its Material and 
Technical Department, hitherto located at the metropolitan Pekin 
Hotel, seems to have been plagued by...cockroaches, mice, and 
other rodents which have proliferated in great numbers. The FCS 
is no less concerned about the deplorable physical condition of 
the "guest house:" In many places the peeling plaster threatens 
to fall right onto one's head. Aware of their responsibility 
for the Motherland, the management of the famous hotel decided 
to close down for a major renovation and sanitation cleaning. 
Therefore the FCS had to look for a new place. 
  This time the intelligence people took a liking to the Mir 
hotel [across from the U.S. Embassy] where not an extra speck of 
dust can be found, let alone cockroaches! The conclusion of a 
secret 10-year leasing agreement is in the final stages, whereby 
the FCS Material and Technical Department will have eight floors 
in the Mir -- from the fourth to the 11th. 

</TEXT>

