<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Legal Proceedings Against Gaydar Postponed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Legal Proceedings Against Gaydar Postponed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2906110594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1015 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2906110594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Legal proceedings against the leader of Russia's 
Democratic Choice, Yegor Gaydar, on charges of slander planned 
for June 29 failed to take place because Gaydar's representative 
failed to appear in court. The appeal was initiated by leader 
of the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia (LDPR), Vladimir 
Zhirinovskiy. Legal proceedings will be held on July 7, the 
court decided. 
  Gaydar's representative, his lawyer Genri Reznik sent a 
notification to the court saying that he was overloaded with 
current affairs, that he had to go on a trip on business and 
that he would go on holiday from July 26. Reznik asked to 
postpone the proceedings and demanded that they be held not 
earlier than September 10. 
  Zhirinovskiy initiated an appeal against Gaydar after Gaydar 
published the article "A Stake on Villains" in the IZVESTIYA 
newspaper. In the article Gaydar called Zhirinovskiy a "fascist 
populist." 

</TEXT>

