<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Orders Reimbursement of Terror Victims </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Orders Reimbursement of Terror Victims </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2806121194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 28 Jun 94 
First Edition p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PM2806121194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Edict No. 1324 of the Russian Federation President "On </F>
Guarantees of Citizens' Rights and Freedoms in the Russian 
Federation," dated Moscow, the Kremlin, 22 June 1994 and signed 
by Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin] 
  [Text] For the purposes of ensuring the realization of the 
citizens' rights and freedoms provided for in the Russian 
Federation Laws "On the Rehabilitation of Victims of Political 
Repression" and "On the Payment of Pensions to Citizens Leaving 
To Take Up Permanent Residence Outside the Russian Federation," 
in connection with the appeals to the Human Rights Commission 
under the Russian Federation president received from Citizen 
S.I. Milshteyn and others, and guided by Part 2 of Article 80 of 
the Russian Federation Constitution, I decree that: 
  1. The Russian Federation Government is to approve within 
one month: 
  in fulfillment of Articles 16 and 16-1 of the Russian 
Federation Law "On the Rehabilitation of Victims of Political 
Repression" -- the Statute on the Return of Property Illegally 
Confiscated, Removed, or Otherwise Taken Out of Ownership in 
Connection with Repression, the Reimbursement of Its Value, or 
the Payment of Monetary Compensation, and the Procedure for the 
Payment of Monetary Compensation to Victims of Political 
Repression and for Its Recomputation; 
  in accordance with Article 3 of the Russian Federation Law 
"On the Payment of Pensions to Citizens Leaving To Take Up 
Permanent Residence Outside the Russian Federation" -- the 
Procedure for Paying Pensions to Citizens Leaving To Take Up 
Permanent Residence Outside the Russian Federation. 
  2. The task of monitoring the fulfillment of this edict is 
to be entrusted to the chairman of the Russian Federation 
Government. 
  3. This edict comes into force the moment it is signed. 
  [Signed] B. Yeltsin, president of the Russian Federation. 22 
June 1994. 

</TEXT>

