<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Stresses Need To Eliminate Poverty </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Stresses Need To Eliminate Poverty </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2906101694 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0900 GMT 
29 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2906101694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Boris Yeltsin, who is touring Moscow region, 
today visited the Soyuz Research and Production Association in 
Lyubertsy. During a brief conversation with journalists, the 
president said the political situation has calmed down and is 
gradually returning to normal. The Treaty on Social Accord has 
started to work. 
  Boris Yeltsin thinks it is necessary to focus on 
implementing 
a targeted program for eliminating poverty. The president 
believes the gap between the minimum wage of 20,000 rubles and 
the average wage of 500,000 rubles a month is unacceptable. 
  Boris Yeltsin also said the economic situation in Russia 
will 
stabilize this year. [passage omitted] 
  Answering a question by an INTERFAX correspondent, Boris 
Yeltsin acknowledged that budgetary means for developing the 
defense industry are insufficient. Therefore, nonbudgetary 
means will have to be used. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

