<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gerashchenko Advocates Protectionism for Banks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gerashchenko Advocates Protectionism for Banks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806153394 Moscow Radio Moscow World Service in English 
1100 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2806153394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Moscow World Service </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Only the foreign banks that can boast a first-rate 
reputation and are regarded as reliable partners should be 
attracted to Russia. This has been stated by the chairman of 
Russia's Central Bank, Viktor Gerashchenko. 
  Speaking in Moscow at a conference of the Consultative 
Council for Foreign Investment, he emphasized the necessity to 
preserve protectionism in respect of home banks. 
  Mr. Gerashchenko also said that in 1993 Russia's gold and 
hard currency reserves had tripled. By the first of this month 
they amounted to $5.6 billion. 

</TEXT>

