<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Edict Covers Voucher to Privatization Transition </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Edict Covers Voucher to Privatization Transition </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806183694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1707 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2806183694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Yeltsin has signed a decree "On Measures 
to Protect the Interests of Citizens During the Transition From 
Voucher to Cash Privatization," setting the rules to privatize 
state enterprises until a new state program for post-voucher 
privatization is adopted. 
  The decree says that after July 1 the shares of enterprises 
which have been registered before that deadline shall be sold at 
auctions and stock exchanges. 
  The decree says that the labor collectives of enterprises 
corporatized before July 1 retain all the benefits established 
by the privatization program. 
  The post-voucher privatization program setting the rules of 
privatization as of July 1, 1994 is to be put into effect by a 
presidential decree before June 31. However, according to the 
Deputy Chairman of the State Property Committee Dmitry Vasiliev 
the program had not yet been submitted to President Yeltsin for 
signature late Monday night. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

