<F P=101> Military &amp; Nuclear Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Grachev on Virtues of Armed Forces </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Grachev on Virtues of Armed Forces </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806180794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1508 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2806180794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 28 TASS -- The Russian Armed Forces are 
efficient, controllable, ready to protect the state from any 
encroachments and ensure national security, including in 
peace-making, Russian Defence Minister General of the Army Pavel 
Grachev told graduates of military academies here today. 
  Today's Russia has no enemies, said the defence minister. 
"This is confirmed by major provisions of the Russian military 
doctrine and known by the whole world. However, Russia same as 
any other state has its interests of the military-political and 
geo-strategic position. We have to remember about this and 
proceed from national interests in military building," said 
Pavel Grachev. 
  The minister recalled names of renowned Russian military 
leaders and said they valued the soldier's confidence most. "Be 
more attentive to your subordinates. Remember that an army 
where an soldier believes in his officer has such an advantage 
that cannot be gained with strength, materiel and any other 
thing," said Grachev. 
  The armed forces are interested in social stability and 
civic 
peace. "Unity and accord are necessary for prosperity of the 
state and successful development of the military sphere," said 
the minister. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

