<H3> <TI>   Mid-Sep Deadline Set for Debating 1995 Budget </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mid-Sep Deadline Set for Debating 1995 Budget </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2806120594 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 28 Jun 94 
First Edition p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PM2806120594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Decree No. 132-I SF of the Russian Federation Federal </F>
Assembly Federation Council "On the Draft Federal Law `On the 
Deadline for Submitting the Draft Federal Budget for 1995 to the 
Russian Federation Federal Assembly'," dated Moscow, 2 June 1994 
and signed by V.F. Shumeyko, chairman of the Russian Federation 
Federal Assembly Federation Council, plus undated draft federal 
law "On the Deadline for Submitting the Draft Federal Budget for 
1995 to the Russian Federation Federal Assembly," signed by 
Russian Federation President B.N. Yeltsin] 
  [Text] In accordance with Part 1 of Article 104 of the 
Russian Federation Constitution, for the purposes of 
accelerating the elaboration of the draft federal budget for 
1995 and also to regularize the budget process in the Russian 
Federation, the Federation Council decrees that: 
  The draft federal law "On the Deadline for Submitting the 
Draft Federal Budget for 1995 to the Russian Federation Federal 
Assembly" (appended) is to be sent to the Russian Federation 
Federal Assembly State Duma. 
  [Signed] V.F. Shumeyko, chairman of the Russian Federation 
Federal Assembly Federation Council. 
  Moscow, 2 June 1994. 
<H5>  Draft Federal Law on the Deadline for Submitting the Draft </H5>
Federal Budget for 1995 to the Russian Federation Federal 
Assembly 
  Article 1. The Russian Federation Government is to submit 
the draft federal budget for 1995 to the Russian Federation 
Federal Assembly no later than 15 September 1994. 
  Article 2. The forming of the draft federal budget for 1995 
is directly linked with the elaboration and implementation of 
measures to extricate the country from the economic and 
financial crisis and also with the development and introduction 
of a balanced and harmonious system of financial and budget 
relations between the federal budget and the budgets of the 
components of the Federation. 
  [Signed] B.N. Yeltsin, president of the Russian Federation. 

</TEXT>

