<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Proposes 2 Sep for Russo-Chinese Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Proposes 2 Sep for Russo-Chinese Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806125894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1136 
GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2806125894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Vladimir Solntsev] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 28 Jun -- PRC President Jiang Zemin is to 
pay an official visit to Russia at the beginning of September 
this year. An accord on this was reached during the visit to 
Moscow by Qian Qichen, vice premier of the PRC State Council and 
foreign minister. "We virtually only have to agree on dates with 
you. The month has already been set," Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin said, when he received the head of the Chinese Foreign 
Ministry in the Kremlin today. The Russian president suggested 
that the schedule proposed by the Chinese side be shifted by two 
days and that the summit begin on 2 September. 

</TEXT>

