<H3> <TI>   Rao on Visit, Relations With Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rao on Visit, Relations With Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806182294 </F>
<F P=103> LD2806182294 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] Moscow Ostankino Television First 
Channel Network in Russian at 1100 GMT on 28 June carries a 
report on an interview with Indian Prime Minister Narasimha Rao 
by correspondent Georgiy Kirichatyy in New Delhi. 
  Regarding Indian-Russian relations, Kirichatyy quotes Prime 
Minister Rao as saying, "Relations between Russia and India have 
always been good, but especially since President Yeltsin's visit 
to our country last year. We managed to resolve a number of the 
most difficult questions which arose as a result of the changes 
taking place in Russia. We have now reached the stage where we 
have the opportunity to make faster progress. I hope my visit 
and the various agreements to be signed will give new impetus to 
the development of Russo-Indian ties. Russia and India need 
each other." "They need to work together." 

</TEXT>

