<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Sergey Sidorov: "Russia and Mongolia: </F>
Cooperation in the Security Sphere"] 
  [Text] Regional and international security, the 
strengthening of Mongolia's nuclear-free status, and the fight 
against crime, international terrorism, and trafficking in arms 
and narcotics are the priorities in cooperation between Mongolia 
and Russia in the security sphere as defined by J. Enhsaihan, 
secretary of the Mongolian National Security Council, during his 
visit to Moscow. A joint communique was signed on the results 
of his talks with Russian Federation Security Council Secretary 
Oleg Lobov. 
  Questions relating to the settlement of Mongolia's foreign 
debt and the development of military-technical cooperation were 
also discussed during the talks. An accord was reached on a 
return visit to Ulaanbaatar by the Russian Federation Security 
Council secretary. 

</TEXT>

