<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the "Talks" rubric: "Discussion </F>
on the Two Countries' Security"] 
  [Text] J. Enhsaihan, secretary of the Mongolian National 
Security Council, visited Moscow last week. He was received by 
Oleg Lobov, secretary of the Russian Federation Security 
Council. The conversation was constructive and friendly in 
character and was held in an atmosphere of complete mutual 
understanding. 
  An accord was reached that in the near future the secretary 
of the Russian Federation Security Council will pay a return 
visit to Mongolia during which a memorandum on cooperation 
between the Russian Federation and Mongolia in the national 
security sphere will be signed. 
  The sides listed the following priority areas for 
cooperation: regional and international security, the 
strengthening of Mongolia's nonnuclear status, economic 
security, and the fight against crime, international terrorism, 
and illegal trafficking in weapons and narcotics. 

</TEXT>

