<H3> <TI>   Special Economic Zone To Be Established in Sakhalin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Special Economic Zone To Be Established in Sakhalin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806164894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1309 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2806164894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Russian State Duma Committee on Economic Policy 
and the administration of the Sakhalin Region have agreed to 
draft a law on Sakhalin providing for the establishment of a 
special economic zone on a part of the region's territory, 
Chairman of the State Duma Committee on Economic Policy Sergey 
Glazyev said in Yuzhno-Sakhalinsk when meeting with 
representatives of the local executive and legislative bodies. 
  Glazyev said that the administration could be given the 
right 
to set quotas for fishing independently immediately without 
waiting for the law to be adopted. However, Glazyev stressed 
that enlargement of rights must be followed by greater 
responsibility of the local authorities for the utilization of 
natural resources and for investments into the social 
infrastructure. 

</TEXT>

