<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Buryatia Reintroduces State Regulation of Timber </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Buryatia Reintroduces State Regulation of Timber </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2906103194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 28 Jun 94 
First Edition p 2 </F>

<F P=103> PM2906103194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS report: "When Freedom Is Too Much For You"] </F>
  [Text] State regulation of the timber industry has been 
reintroduced in Buryatia by decision of the republic Council of 
Ministers. The republic government was forced into taking this 
step by the critical situation in this sector, which was rapidly 
privatized two years ago. 
  The newfound freedom turned out to be a heavy burden for the 
15 joint-stock companies formed on the basis of the Transbaykal 
region's timber procurement establishments. Their output proved 
uncompetitive not only in the world market but also in the 
Russian market, as its prime cost is greater than those of its 
nearest rivals in Siberia. 
  Nevertheless, the Government of Buryatia's decision does not 
signal a return to the administrative economic management of the 
sector. The "Lesopromyshlennaya Kompaniya `Zabaykalles'" state 
enterprise will only be a coordinating body. Its main task is 
to coordinate interests of the republic and the joint-stock 
companies and to create a scientifically and economically based 
model of investment in the Transbaykal region's timber industry. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

