<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Willingness To Work With European Initiative Stressed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Willingness To Work With European Initiative Stressed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2906090694 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1900 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2906090694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The status granted to Ukraine of associate council 
member of the Central European Initiative could create favorable 
conditions for Ukraine to acquire full membership of this 
authoritative organization as soon as possible. During a meeting 
with journalists, (Volodymyr Lapytskyy), Ukraine's coordinator 
in this organization, stressed that Ukraine confirmed its 
willingness to take part in the work of the Central European 
Initiative groups on transportation, energy, culture, ecology, 
science, technology, and information. Ukraine pays particular 
attention to cooperation in the sphere of transportation. It is 
already taking part in the construction of the Ukrainian part of 
the Trieste-Budapest-Kiev Trans-European highway. The European 
Bank of Reconstruction and Development is financing this project. 

</TEXT>

