<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kuchma Confident at Post-Election News Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kuchma Confident at Post-Election News Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2906102694 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 2200 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2906102694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 28 Jun -- "I am not yet president and so many 
people have already gathered," said Ukrainian presidential 
candidate Leonid Kuchma opening a news conference on the results 
of the first round of the elections. 
  A representative of the presidential candidate's team at the 
news conference said the outcome of the first round demonstrated 
that "the new course proposed by Kuchma enjoys popularity among 
the people." The candidate himself added: "It also shows that 
most of the other deputies are using none other than my program 
in the preelection contest." 
  Leonid Kuchma underscored that opportunities to use the 
state 
mass media in the preelection campaign were not equal. Asked 
about his own use of the private mass media in Donetsk and Kiev 
and his appearance on Ostankino TV, Mr. Kuchma replied that 
"Leonid Kravchuk did it on a much larger scale". 
  The outcome of the election in Crimea was described by Mr. 
Kuchma as crucial. There, as we know, over 83 percent of the 
electorate voted in favor of his candidacy. "Crimea has proved 
to be an absolutely normal part of Ukraine," Leonid Kuchma said. 
  "My aim is not winning. My aim is, under the conditions of 
an information blockade, communicating to the public at large my 
own views and opinions on the situation in the state," Leonid 
Kuchma concluded. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

