<H3> <TI>   Sevastopol To Suspend Activities of Mission </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sevastopol To Suspend Activities of Mission </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2906082494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0737 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2906082494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By UKRINFORM correspondent Mikhail Stetsyuk for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Sevastopol June 29 TASS -- The results of elections 
of the city mayor and deputies to the Sevastopol City Council 
were discussed at a session of the Electoral Commission on 
Tuesday. The mandates won by 50 deputies and chairman of the 
executive committee Viktor Semenov were recognised valid. 
  Viktor Semenov, in his first address as the city mayor, said 
that the new power would be tough and its goal would be to 
improve the life of city residents. Semenov pledged to suspend 
the activities of the Ukrainian president's mission in 
Sevastopol on the very first day when the newly elected city 
council comes into office, saying that organs of state 
administration would begin to operate in accordance with a 
regime of the executive committee of the city council of 
people's deputies. 
  Semenov intends to put problems, pertaining to the 
possibility of Sevastopol's integration into the Crimean common 
economic space, on the agenda of the first session of the city 
council. In this connection, the city council shall appeal to 
the president and the parliament of the autonomous republic in 
order to apply the banking, currency and customs policy pursued 
by the Crimean authorities, on the city's territory. 
  The new mayor intends to endorse the city's emblem and its 
anthem at the first session of the city council. 

</TEXT>

