<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Assembly Urges Referendum on Confederation With Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Assembly Urges Referendum on Confederation With Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2806115094 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1600 
GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2806115094 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] BELINFORM has been told by [name indistinct], head 
of the press service of the Belaya Rus-Slav Assembly Party, that 
early in July the Russian State Duma plans to discuss the 
possibility of creating a confederation between Belarus and 
Russia. Representatives of this party were invited to attend the 
discussion. 
  The Belaya Rus-Slav Assembly press service also reported 
that 
the Party Duma addresses the Belarusian Supreme Soviet with a 
proposal to hold -- during the second round of presidential 
elections -- a referendum with regard to rendering official 
status to the Russian language in Belarus, the creation of a 
confederation with Russia, and the introduction of dual, 
Belarusian-Russian, citizenship. 

</TEXT>

