<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll: Support for Merger, Opposition to Sovereignty Loss </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll: Support for Merger, Opposition to Sovereignty Loss </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2906084694 Minsk SEM DNEY in Russian 25 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> WS2906084694 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk SEM DNEY </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Nikolay Levchuk: "Sovereignty, Anyway!"] </F>
  [Text] According to a poll conducted by the "West-East" 
Strategic Initiatives Center, 76.4 percent of the Belarusian 
people support the unification of the Belarusian and Russian 
monetary systems. 
  If the unification results in a ceding of powers to the 
Russian Government or Central Bank, the move will be supported 
by 39.6 percent of society. If the unification results in a 
loss of Belarusian sovereignty, only 24.5 will support this 
initiative. 

</TEXT>

