<F P=102>   AU2806160794 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2140 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2806160794 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau, BASAPRESS, 25/06/1994 -- "Many political 
games surround the Gagauz problem," stated Nikolai Telpiz, 
Gagauz deputy speaker, to BASA, commenting on the results of the 
meeting between Gagauz legislators and the Socialist Unity 
faction on the "Gagauz Eri" project. According to him, Comrat 
representatives were surprised "to hear the proposal to discuss 
a draft on special juridical status modified by the Moldovan 
Parliamentary Commission and not the one previously drafted by 
the Moldovan and Gagauz Parliamentary commissions." Valeriu 
Senic, Socialist Unity faction leader, chatted on the Socialist 
Unity faction representatives to support the modifications 
proposed by the Moldovan Parliamentary commission. "The Gagauz 
Parliamentary Commission sent a protest to the Moldovan 
Parliamentary Commission which unilaterally modified the draft 
law; the draft does not favor the Gagauz side and limits the 
potency of the `Gagauz Eri -- Gagauzia'." 

</TEXT>

