<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Increase in National Income, Industrial Output Seen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Increase in National Income, Industrial Output Seen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2806192094 Yerevan SNARK in English 2003 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2806192094 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, June 28 (SNARK) -- Armenia is the only 
country in CIS where the growth of basic economic indicators is 
observed. According to the State Statistical Administration data 
published in Yerevan today, the produced national income during 
the five months of this year has increased as compared to the 
corresponding period last year by 7.5 percent and the volume of 
industrial output grew by 12 percent. 
  At the same time, say specialists, such a growth indicates 
only insignificant improvement in the state of economy where a 
steep slump was observed in 1992-93. 
  Due to the permanent blockade of communications and 
insolvency, Armenia, still experiences a shortage of raw 
materials and electricity and the life level of the republic 
continues to remain the lowest among the CIS countries. 

</TEXT>

