<F P=100> BALTIC STATES </F>
<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Not To Renew Soviet-Era Passports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Not To Renew Soviet-Era Passports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2906092894 Tallinn ETA in English 1404 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2906092894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["News Release"] </F>
  [Text] Soviet-time "red passports" expire on July 1 as the 
government decided not to renew them, Prime Minister Mart Laar 
told a government briefing on Tuesday. 
  All Estonian citizens should by now hold Estonian passports 
and older people who have not obtained a new passport should 
have no difficulties in receiving their benefits as post 
stations would accept old passports as ID's, Laar said. 
  Laar also said that by September a booklet would be issued 
for foreigners in Estonia where they can find information on 
applying for a foreigners' passport, Estonian citizenship, etc. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

