<H3> <TI>   Canada's Ouellet Backs Call for Russian Withdrawal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Canada's Ouellet Backs Call for Russian Withdrawal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806182194 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 1600 
GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2806182194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network </F>
<F P=105>  Estonian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Foreign Minister Juri Luik has met with Canadian 
Foreign Minister Andre Ouellet in Ottawa. Mr. Ouellet stated 
that he supports the Estonian call for Russian troop withdrawal 
by the end of August. He also promised support to Estonia at 
the top international level. The Estonian and Canadian foreign 
ministers signed a bilateral business and trade agreement, 
designed to encourage the development of trade contacts between 
the two countries. 
  Juri Luik made a speech at the Canadian center for world 
security on the subject of Estonian-Russian relations and 
security issues in the Baltic region. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

