<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Military Permits Extended to 31 Aug </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Military Permits Extended to 31 Aug </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2906101094 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 0900 GMT 29 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2906101094 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>
<F P=105>  Latvian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The time is approaching for the complete withdrawal 
of Russian forces from Latvia. A decision was made at a 
government session which has just taken place, on permission for 
Russian military personnel and members of their families to stay 
until 31 August. We asked Ilgonis Upmalis, head of the 
government commission for monitoring the withdrawal of the 
Russian Army, to comment. 
  [Begin Upmalis recording] So far, permits of stay have been 
valid until 30 June. As the stipulated period is expiring and 
the deadline for the withdrawal set in interstate agreements is 
31 August, amendments were made today to the previous decision, 
and it was stipulated that permits to stay have been extended 
until 31 August 1994. The procedure is that, Army units have to 
submit lists of military personnel, as well as lists of members 
of families, who have these permits to stay. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

