<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Miners at 5 Mines in Donetsk Begin Strike </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Miners at 5 Mines in Donetsk Begin Strike </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806193594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1839 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2806193594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On Tuesday miners of five mines of Ordzhonikidzeugol 
corporation in Yenakiyevo, Donetsk coal basin, went on strike 
demanding payment of delayed wages, disability benefits and 
holiday bonuses. They also demand the dismissal of the general 
director of the corporation Aleksandr Poshtuk. The labor action 
is led by the Independent Miners' Union, one of the biggest in 
Ukraine. 
  According to the local strike committee, miners have not 
been 
paid since April at many facilities. Donetskugol corporation 
has not been paying its employees since May. 
  On Tuesday the Ukrainian parliament was told that the reason 
for the labor action at Pervomaiskugol mining corporation in the 
Lugansk Region was the same. There, miners refused to return to 
the surface after the shift. 
  According to Interfax-Ukraine, the miners' wages are between 
three and five million karbovantsy ($70-$120) a month. 

</TEXT>

