<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister: Nagorno-Karabakh `De Facto' Part of Armenia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister: Nagorno-Karabakh `De Facto' Part of Armenia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2806191994 Yerevan SNARK in English 2003 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2806191994 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, 28 June. (SNARK) -- Armenian Internal 
Affairs Minister, Vano Siradegyan, announced in an interview 
published today by the "HAYASTANI HANRAPETUTYUN" ("REPUBLIC OF 
ARMENIA") newspaper that Nagorno-Karabakh has been de facto 
incorporated in Armenia. Though the region is the place where 
clash the interests of super- powers, "they cannot ignore the 
organized nation which is ready to fight", said Mr. Siradegyan. 
At the same time, the minister opposed the fanning of "military 
hysteria" in Armenia which, in his opinion,"may discredit the 
state". 
  The major mission of his department the minister called 
preservation of political stability in Armenia until the new 
election campaign. By his words, "Armenia cannot allow itself 
early elections, forced resignations, and other social shocks". 

</TEXT>

