<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moscow Concerned Over Situation in Yemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moscow Concerned Over Situation in Yemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2906162294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1608 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2906162294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Yuriy Tyssovskiy] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 29 TASS -- Talks between Russian Foreign 
Minister Andrey Kozyrev and Foreign Minister of the Yemeni 
Republic Muhammad Salim Basindawa who arrived in Moscow on 
Wednesday, began at the building of the Russian Foreign Ministry 
today. 
  It is expected that later today the head of the Russian 
foreign office will hold talks with South Yemeni emissary -- 
Deputy Secretary General of the Central Committee of the Yemeni 
Socialist Party Saleh Saleh Muhammad. 
  Valerian Shuvayev, head of the section of countries on the 
Arabian Peninsula and the department of the Middle East and 
north Africa of the Russian Foreign ministry, told ITAR-TASS 
about Moscow's position at the talks. 
  These contacts, he said, are being carried out within the 
framework of Russian diplomacy's efforts aimed at reaching a 
ceasefire between the confronting sides in Yemen which would 
become the first step towards halting a bloodshed. 
  All internal problems of this Arab country must be resolved 
at a negotiating table. We are prepared to coordinate our 
actions with all who seek to achieve the same aims, both on a 
bilateral basis and within the framework of the United Nations 
to promote the soonest stopping of the senseless fratricidal 
war, the Russian diplomat pointed out. 

</TEXT>

