<F P=103> BK2906161594 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The prime minister, Mr. P.V. Narasimha Rao, arrived 
in Moscow a short while ago. He was received by at the airport 
by the Russian prime minister, Mr. Chernomyrdin, and a host of 
other prominent Russian leaders, including the minister of state 
for foreign affairs and the Russia ambassador to India. The 
Indian ambassador, Mr. R. Sen, and other members of the mission 
were also present. Our special correspondent, I.J. Behal, 
reports from Moscow that the prime minister was presented a 
guard of honor by the contingents of the three services. The 
prime minister will be accorded a ceremonial welcome tomorrow 
morning at St. George's Hall at the Kremlin, which will be 
followed by talks with President Yeltsin. 

