<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on Visit by IAEA's Blix </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets With Primakov </H4>

<F P=102> MK3006071094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 30 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> MK3006071094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SEGODNYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [SEGODNYA report: "IAEA Establishes Contacts With the FIS"] </F>
  [Text] Yevgeniy Primakov, director of the Russian Foreign 
Intelligence Service [FIS], met yesterday with IAEA General 
Director Hans Blix, who is in Moscow on an official visit, the 
FIS press bureau has said. The collection of information about 
the proliferation and development of weapons of mass destruction 
has always been among special services' priority tasks, and the 
IAEA draws on intelligence data of the U.S. and British 
intelligence services it has been receiving not only through 
their governments; this is why Mr. Blix is also planning to 
establish close cooperation with the Russian intelligence 
service. 

</TEXT>

