<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Visit by IAEA's Blix </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on Visit by IAEA's Blix </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Further on Primakov Meeting </H4>

<F P=102> LD2906123294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1135 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2906123294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Olga Semenova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 29 TASS -- Hans Blix, director of the 
International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA), met with Director of 
the Russian Foreign Intelligence Service (SVR) Yevgeniy Primakov 
on Wednesday and sources in the SRV indicated that Blix wants 
Russian intelligence information on nuclear non-proliferation 
problem. 
  "The Foreign Intelligence has never concealed that 
monitoring 
the proliferation of nuclear weapons is among our priority 
tasks", a high ranking intelligence official told TASS. 
  He added that the IAEA relies in its activities on the 
information received from us and British secret services not 
only through their corresponding governments, but also directly 
from the intelligence bodies. 
  "It is quite logical that the IAEA director intends to 
establish closer cooperation in the given field with the Russian 
intelligence as well in order to get a more objective picture", 
the official said adding that the "exchange of such information 
is in mutual interests". 

</TEXT>

