<H3> <TI>   Kaliningrad Orders Construction of New Port </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kaliningrad Orders Construction of New Port </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2906140194 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 28 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PM2906140194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by correspondent Valeriy Gromak: "Baltiysk Will </F>
Become an International Port"] 
  [Text] Baltiysk -- Kaliningrad Oblast Administration chief 
Yuriy Matochkin has signed a Decree "On the Implementation of 
Preparatory Work for the Design and Construction of a Port 
Complex in Baltiysk." It instructs the Baltic Fleet command, 
the Baltiysk administration, and the Kaliningrad port maritime 
administration to set up a commission to define the boundaries 
of the area for the construction of the port complex and to 
transfer the defined area, together with hydraulic engineering 
installations, to the use of the maritime administration. The 
decree also instructs that proposals and a package of documents 
on opening the commercial port of Baltiysk to foreign ships be 
prepared and submitted to the Ministry of Transport. 

</TEXT>

