<H3> <TI>   Official Views Delegation Tasks at UN Council Session </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Views Delegation Tasks at UN Council Session </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2906124994 Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY in Ukrainian 28 Jun 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> AU2906124994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Difficult Work Is Ahead of Us"] </F>
  [Text] A session of the UN Economic and Social Council 
opened in New York yesterday. In terms of significance, it 
occupies third place in the structure of the United Nations 
after the General Assembly and the Security Council. Ukraine is 
a member of the UN Economic and Social Council and participates 
in all its sessions. 
  "This time, our delegation must raise, first and foremost, 
the questions of social and economic development of the 
Ukrainian state, the course of reforms, and the assistance to 
these processes on the part of the United Nations," said First 
Deputy Minister of Foreign Affairs Mykola Makarevych. "Besides, 
we must also draw the attention of the world community to two 
problems that are important and painful for us -- the presently 
effective UN sanctions against the former Yugoslavia and the 
size of Ukraine's monetary contribution to the United Nations. 
We will again insist that it is primarily the civilian 
population that suffers from the sanctions. That is why we 
attach great importance to either canceling the sanctions or 
minimizing them. Regarding contributions, very complicated work 
is envisioned. We are not only indebted to the United Nations, 
but also to other international organizations. Even though the 
percentage is, in fact, exceedingly high for Ukraine, the money 
must be paid. In this direction, we will continue to elaborate 
a mechanism enabling us to correctly calculate the size of our 
contributions and submit the relevant information to the United 
Nations." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

