<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on Cuban Official's Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on Cuban Official's Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Signs Merchant Shipping Agreement </H4>

<F P=102> LD2906184994 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1600 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2906184994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 29 June Lionel Soto, vice president of the 
Council of Ministers of the Republic of Cuba, who is on an 
official visit to Ukraine, and Ukraine's Transport Minister 
Orest Klympush signed a merchant shipping agreement. There has 
long been a need for this document, Lionel Soto said. I am 
convinced that the agreement initiates a new stage in our 
relations. As of today we can carry on trade right across the 
sea, because Cuba is an island state and this is the only way to 
communicate with the outside world. 

</TEXT>

