<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on Cuban Official's Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on Cuban Official's Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Comments on Economic Needs </H4>

<F P=102> LD2906184394 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1600 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2906184394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The leader of a Cuban governmental delegation, Vice 
President of the Council of Ministers of the Republic of Cuba 
Lionel Soto, referred to his delegation's visit to Ukraine as 
very important. 
  At a news conference in Kiev, Lionel Soto pointed out that 
the main objective of the visit was to restore all the economic 
relations which Ukraine and Cuba maintained during the Soviet 
Union's existence. After the disintegration of the USSR, he 
pointed out, these relations have been almost abolished. 
  The head of the Cuban governmental delegation also declared 
that there are no political differences between our two states 
and that our peoples are friendly peoples. 
  At present, Lionel Soto said, we must get down to specific 
work on developing our relations. 

</TEXT>

