<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moroz, French Envoy Discuss Economics, Chernobyl </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moroz, French Envoy Discuss Economics, Chernobyl </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2906212694 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1900 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2906212694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 29 June Oleksandr Moroz, chairman of Ukraine's 
Supreme Council, received Michel-Yves Peissik, French ambassador 
to Ukraine. Issues related to the development of 
Ukrainian-French relations were discussed during the 
conversation. Much attention was paid to ways of encouraging 
French investment in Ukraine's economy. Whoever is the first to 
do this will gain a higher profit, Moroz stressed. 
  Among the major topics discussed was the issue of 
eliminating 
the consequences of the Chernobyl accident. Chernobyl is a 
misfortune not only for the Ukrainian people. The world 
community should understand that this is a matter of concern for 
all. It is necessary to resolutely move from declarations to 
concrete assistance, Moroz declared. 
  Peissik said that a representative of France's prime 
minister 
is expected to arrive in Ukraine in early July. This visit will 
be entirely dedicated to the Chernobyl issue. During the talks 
they also discussed ways of expanding Ukrainian-French 
interparliamentary relations. 

</TEXT>

