<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kuchma Demands Access to Media for Election Campaign </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kuchma Demands Access to Media for Election Campaign </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2906142294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1221 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2906142294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Leonid Kuchma, a Ukrainian presidential candidate, 
filed a protest with the Ukrainian Central Electoral Commission 
and the Supreme Soviet Presidium, saying that the 
state-controlled media gave access only to incumbent President 
Leonid Kuchma. [as received] 
  In particular, he wrote that the Ukrainian television 
promoted Leonid Kravchuk even on election day, 26 June, in 
flagrant violation of the law. 
  Kuchma won nearly 32 percent and Kravchuk nearly 38 percent 
in the first round of presidential elections. 

</TEXT>

