<H3> <TI>   Lukashenko Wins 44.82 Percent in 1st Round </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lukashenko Wins 44.82 Percent in 1st Round </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2906133094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1221 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2906133094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The major contenders for the Belarussian 
[Belarusian] presidency Aleksandr Lukashenko and Vyacheslav 
Kebich have collected correspondingly 44.82 percent and 17.33 
percent of the votes in the course of the first round of the 
presidential elections in Belarus held on 23 June. 
  According to official information from the Central Electoral 
Commission, their names will be put on ballot-papers for the 
second round of voting. 
  The Central Electoral Commission is to announce its final 
decision on the date of the elections on Thursday, however, 
according to a preliminary opinion of the commission's leaders 
it will be held on Sunday, 10 June. 
  Ivan Likhach, secretary of the Central Electoral Commission, 
reported to Interfax that "in the course of verification of the 
first round of voting the commission has not found any 
violations which would give reason to hold an investigation." 

</TEXT>

