<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS freelance correspondent Anatoliy Khologyuk] </F>
  [Text] Tiraspol, 30 Jun (TASS) -- The special state of 
affairs in the Dniester republic has been extended from 1 July 
through 31 August this year. This was made public in a decree 
by Dniester President Igor Smirnov which was broadcast on 
Dniester republic radio on Wednesday [29 June] evening. The 
main motives for extending the special state of affairs, it 
states in the decree, are to help the militia wage the organized 
struggle against crime and to preserve the state system of the 
Dniester-Moldovan republic. 
  Ivan Fuchidzhi, acting minister of internal affairs of the 
Dniester republic, was in favor of the special state of affairs 
being extended in the region. He reported to the ITAR-TASS 
correspondent that the special state of affairs will help the 
militia bodies to purposefully wage the organized struggle 
against crime in the region that has been stepped up of late 
both in Tiraspol and other regions. 

</TEXT>

