<H3> <TI>   Talks Representative on Release of Prisoners </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Talks Representative on Release of Prisoners </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806211294 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in 
Persian 1630 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2806211294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] [Correspondent] We are speaking with Mr. 
Shukurjon Zuhurov, representative of Tajikistan. Mr. Zuhurov, 
representatives of the opposition groups have stated that 
simultaneously with a ceasefire a nationwide amnesty ought to be 
declared. However, the representatives of the state of 
Tajikistan were against this proposal. What was the reason for 
this opposition? 
  [Zuhurov, heard briefly speaking in Tajik, fading into 
Persian translation] The reason for this is as follows: We 
fully agree with this condition. However, we said that we need 
time so that we can return to our country and approach the 
related bodies to look into the cases of those against whom 
criminal proceedings have been issued and to release them from 
prison over a period of time. A document must be formulated and 
a law must be adopted for this. This will require five to 10 
days, or two to three weeks. 

</TEXT>

