<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridneva] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe, 29 Jun -- At about 2300 on Tuesday a 
border detail in the sector of the 12th border outpost of the 
Moscow border detachment was subjected to intense shelling. 
  The Russian border guards returned fire and neutralized the 
firing points. There were no casualties among the Russian 
border guards. An ITAR-TASS correspondent found this out from 
informed military sources in Dushanbe. This is already the 
third case this week of firing on Russian border guard 
detachments and border posts from Afghan territory. 

