<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Compromise Reached Over Humanitarian Aid for Pamir </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Compromise Reached Over Humanitarian Aid for Pamir </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2906211894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1305 
GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2906211894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridneva] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe, 29 Jun -- The convoy of trucks carrying 
humanitarian cargo for the inhabitants of the Pamirs 
successfully surmounted the Khabu-Rabot mountain pass today and 
moved on toward Khorog, the administrative center of the 
Gorno-Badakhshan autonomous oblast of Tajikistan. An ITAR-TASS 
correspondent has learned from informed sources in the oblast 
administration that the units of the Collective Peace-keeping 
Forces (CPF) deployed in Tajikistan have remained on the far 
side of the pass. The protection of the convoy and the safety 
of the drivers was undertaken by units of the mountain rifle 
battalion of the republic's Ministry of Defense which is manned 
by young people from the Pamirs and also by self-defense units 
of Gorno-Badakhshan oblast. 
  This agreement was reached during talks between 
representatives of the CPF command, local authorities of 
Gorno-Badakhshan oblast, representatives of the coalition 
council of democratic forces, and some field commanders of 
self-defense units. In the opinion of Ulfat-khanum, one of the 
representatives of the coalition council of the autonomous 
region, the initial decision by the CPF command to accompany the 
humanitarian cargo across the territory of the oblast right to 
Khorog aroused serious concern among the public of the Pamirs. 
They thought there might be provocations from individual forces 
interested in destabilizing the situation in the Pamirs. 
Ulfat-khanum stressed that this concern had been conveyed to the 
CPF command and also to the representative of the UN mission in 
the oblast centre of Khorog and, as a result, a sensible 
compromise had been reached. 
  It is expected that the convoy of trucks carrying foodstuffs 
will arrive in Khorog by this evening. The aid is very timely 
aince the population of Gorno-Badakhshan autonomous oblast is on 
the verge of starvation. Food reserves are virtually exhausted. 
The only bakery in the administrative center has been out of 
action for several days because there is no flour. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-42045 </DOCNO>
