<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Claims of Azerbaijani Military Activity Denied </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Claims of Azerbaijani Military Activity Denied </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2906144294 Baku TURAN in English 1254 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2906144294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku, June 28 (TURAN) -- Baku is deeply concerned 
about the statements repeatedly distributed by Armenians 
officials in Yerevan and Khankendi (Stepanakert), which report 
that "Azerbaijan prepares an offensive towards 
Nagorno-Karabakh", an employee of Azerbaijan's Presidential 
staff told TURAN. 
  "Such irresponsible statements do not allow to create 
favourable conditions for settlement of the Armenian-Azerbaijani 
conflict. Both parties to the conflict have to be responsible 
for their activities", reports the same source. 
  The Republic of Azerbaijan calls upon the Armenian 
authorities and the heads of Armenian community of 
Nagorno-Karabakh not to break the peace settlement process and 
not to destabilize the situation. 
  On June 25 ITAR-TASS referring to military leaders of 
Nagorno-Karabakh distributed a statement about Azerbaijan's 
preparations to a large-scale offensive. 

</TEXT>

