<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aliyev Arrives in Iran on Official Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aliyev Arrives in Iran on Official Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2906161294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1324 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2906161294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Oleg Kuzmin] </F>
  [Text] Tehran June 29 TASS -- President of Azerbaijan 
Geydar Aliyev arrived in the Iranian capital Tehran on a 
four-day official visit today. At Tehran's Mehrabad airport, 
Aliyev told journalists that "Azerbaijan regards Iran as a 
powerful and influential neighbour, and is ready to develop 
cooperation with it in all spheres." 
  Aliyev said he will hold talks with Iranian President 'Ali 
Akbar- Rafsanjani and other Iranian leaders to discuss issues of 
regional and world policy as well as prospects for expanding 
bilateral relations between the two countries. 
  Receiving Aliyev, Hashemi-Rafsanjani emphasised the 
historical, religious and ethnic closeness of the two people. 
The Iranian head of state noted that many accords, which were 
achieved during the Iranian president's visit to Baku last year, 
are in the stage of implementation, and the remaining will 
require some time to be put into life. The Iranian president 
also expressed concern over the unabated bloodshed in the 
Trans-Caucasus region. 

</TEXT>

