<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karabakh Says Turkish Mediator Role Unacceptable </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karabakh Says Turkish Mediator Role Unacceptable </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2906182794 Yerevan SNARK in English 1346 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2906182794 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Stepanakert, June 29. (SNARK)--The Republic of 
Nagorno-Karabakh is anxious with the appeals of the Azerbaijani 
side to enlarge the range of active intermediaries in the 
process of the Karabakh-Azerbaijani conflict regulation owing to 
reinforcement of the Turkey's role. 
  The Karabakh Foreign Affairs Department told SNARK Turkey's 
attempts show the official Baku's intention to blockade the 
Russia's peace-keeping attempts to reach a deadlock in the 
peace-making process. 
  The Karabakh side for numerous times declared the 
unacceptability of the Turkey's intermediary instigating role 
which is of the pro-Azerbaijani character cannot be considered 
neutral. 

</TEXT>

