<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Patsatsia Denies Refugees Arriving in Gali Region </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Patsatsia Denies Refugees Arriving in Gali Region </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2906202594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1758 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2906202594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Georgian Prime-Minister Otar Patsatsia has 
categorically denied Abkhaz reports about the beginning of the 
mass uncontrolled arrival of Georgian refugees in the Gali 
region. At a meeting with the local administration and law 
enforcement officers in Zugdidi on Wednesday he said false 
reports are spread to undermine the normal return of refugees. 
  The prime-minister said that the most important stage after 
the appearance of peace-keeping forces in the security zone is 
the return of refugees. Any obstacles to the process should be 
removed. Everything is going to be done in keeping with the 
four-sided agreements. 

</TEXT>

