<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Waigel Urges FDP To Back Bugging Against Crime </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Waigel Urges FDP To Back Bugging Against Crime </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3005111594 Hamburg BILD AM SONNTAG in German 29 May 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> AU3005111594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg BILD AM SONNTAG </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Guest Commentary" by Theo Waigel, finance minister and </F>
Christian Social Union chairman: "Bugging Campaign: The FDP 
Must Join In"] 
  [Text] The apartment of the normal citizen is sacred to 
all of us. However, that of the drug boss and gangster king 
must not remain closed to the police. Just as in other 
rule-of-law states around us, the police must be able in the 
future to bug German apartments for reconnaissance purposes if 
new crimes are being discussed there. 
  Therefore, I appeal to the delegates of the Free Democratic 
Party [FDP] congress, which begins in Rostock next week, to give 
a signal for the introduction of the great bugging campaign in 
Germany. The population and certainly the majority of the FDP 
followers expect this from their party. Therefore, I hope that 
at the end of the week, the path will be free so that the police 
can combat crimes even more successfully on the basis of clear 
rules of the rule-of-law state, which make arbitrariness 
impossible. 
  The past has clearly shown that, without the great bugging 
campaign to gain evidence, we cannot successfully combat 
international crime in the long run. Therefore, we must act 
together. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

