<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Calls For UN Alternatives to CBM's </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Calls For UN Alternatives to CBM's </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC3005120094 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1030 GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC3005120094 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Government spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis confirmed 
that the Cyprus Government expects the UN secretary general's 
report to be issued tomorrow. He added that the government 
believes that it will be an objective report that will record 
the facts that attribute blame to the Turkish side. He also 
noted that the confidence-building measures [CBM's] issue has 
ended. Mr. Kasoulidhis further said that the government does 
not see any reason for President Glavkos Kliridhis, who is 
visiting New York, to discuss the CBM's with the UN secretary 
general. 
  The spokesman added: The Cyprus Government believes that the 
Security Council should find other ways to participate in the 
process of promoting a Cyprus solution. He also made it clear 
that the government desires to participate in any of those 
alternative plans of action, which should be decided by the 
Security Council on the basis of Resolution 889. 

</TEXT>

