<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kliridhis on Cyprus-Greece Defense Doctrine </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC3005115994 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1030 GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC3005115994 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] President Glavkos Kliridhis stressed that the 
decision falls within the joint Cyprus-Greece defense doctrine 
whether to build air, navy, or other bases in Cyprus. President 
Kliridhis made the statement after his meeting at the 
Presidential Palace today with Lieutenant General Alevromayiros, 
first deputy chief of the Greek Army General Staff. He also 
expressed full satisfaction over the joint Cyprus-Greece defense 
doctrine and noted that at the meeting they also exchanged views 
on the doctrine, adding that both sides are proceeding with the 
preparation of a Cyprus defense plan. 
  President Kliridhis also referred to the Turkish plan, which 
was revealed by the Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation last night, 
aimed at justifying their rejection of the confidence-building 
measures [CBM's] by creating the impression that the coexistence 
of Greek and Turkish Cypriots is impossible. The president 
expressed the conviction that the Turks will not succeed in 
justifying their positions because, he stressed, it is well 
known that there have been no provocations by the Greek Cypriot 
side. He added: The Turkish side rejected the CBM's because of 
a lack of political will. 
  Lt. Gen. Alevromayiros expressed thanks to the Cyprus 
Government for the material and moral support it renders to 
ELDIK [Greek Forces of Cyprus]. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

