<F P=102>   NC2605122894 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1030 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2605122894 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Glavkos Kliridhis stressed that Cyprus is 
not seeking free entrance into the European Union [EU], but 
wants to fulfill the expectations of its role and its 
contribution to the world order being created. 
  Addressing a high-level conference on EU law which began 
this 
morning in Nicosia, the president said Cyprus is fully committed 
to its European orientation because it believes in the role, the 
mission, and the need for the EU. He added that Cyprus asks for 
nothing more than to be a republic that applies to the whole of 
Cyprus' territory, something that cannot happen now because of 
the de facto division imposed and maintained by the presence of 
Turkish troops and settlers. 
  European personalities, distinguished judges of the EU 
court, 
senior officials, and academicians from EU member states are 
participating in the two-day conference. 

</TEXT>

