<H3> <TI>   Talks With Moscow on Telecommunications Conclude </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Talks With Moscow on Telecommunications Conclude </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2705185494 Nicosia CYPRUS NEWS AGENCY in English 1600 GMT 
27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2705185494 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia CYPRUS NEWS AGENCY </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nicosia, May 27 (CNA)--Russia and Cyprus held talks 
this week in Moscow on bilateral issues concerning 
telecommunications and postal services. 
  The talks were conducted between Communications and Works 
Minister Adhamos Adhamidhis and Russian officials during 
Adhamidhis' eight-day visit to Moscow, which ended this morning. 
  Discussions focused on the possibility of amending an 
existing bilateral agreement on air transport to allow an 
increase of the respective national carriers, from one to two. 
  A Russian delegation is expected to visit Cyprus soon to 
examine in detail the repercussions of such a move. 
  Direct satellite telecommunications links were also on the 
agenda of the talks, during which the two sides expressed 
satisfaction with this facility. 
  Cyprus suggested that its network is used to link Russia 
with 
Syria, Lebanon, Israel, Greece, Egypt and Saudi Arabia. The 
matter will be discussed further at a later stage. 
  The ministers decided to organise a joint philatelic 
exhibition and possibly issue a common series of stamps. 

</TEXT>

