<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Clarifies Papandreou Statements on Albania </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Clarifies Papandreou Statements on Albania </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2805160594 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1500 GMT 28 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2805160594 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Government Spokesman Evangelos Venizelos today 
repeated Greece's desire to improve its relations with Albania 
and stressed that this improvement inevitably depends on respect 
for the rights of the Greeks of Albania. Venizelos stressed: 
We have legal political and diplomatic means at our disposal 
which we will use if we find ourselves in a position to do so. 
The international community and Albanian Government know very 
well what these means are, he said. 
  The spokesman made the above statement when he was asked by 
correspondents in Thessaloniki to clarify Prime Minister Andreas 
Papandreou's statement made on Mega Channel to the effect that 
there are other measures our country can take if the Albanian 
side continues with the same stance. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

