<H3> <TI>   Officials React to Albanian Minister Serreqi's Remarks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Officials React to Albanian Minister Serreqi's Remarks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2705174694 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1500 GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2705174694 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Albanian Foreign Minister Alfred Serreqi made some 
provocative remarks from the floor of the Conference on 
Stability in Europe, being held in Paris. Serreqi spoke about 
the extreme nationalist stance taken by Greece, which is 
affecting the Greek minority in Albania and described the 
guidance, as he put it, given the North Ipirus citizens as 
unacceptable. 
  Deputy Foreign Minister Yeoryios Papandreou, who met with 
Serreqi on the sidelines of the conference, reacted strongly. 
Papandeou protested the Albanian foreign minister's remarks and 
against the arrests of North Ipirotans. Serreqi denied that any 
arrests had taken place. 
  Alternate Foreign Minister Theodhoros Pangalos and 
Papandreou 
described Albania's stance as paranoid. The Athens Television 
Network correspondent in Gjirokaster reports that more North 
Ipirotans were arrested last night and today, and were taken to 
court. 

</TEXT>

