<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cetin Departs for European Stability Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cetin Departs for European Stability Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2505190694 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2505190694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin left for Paris today 
to attend the opening conference of the European Stability Pact. 
In a predeparture statement at Ankara's Esenboga Airport, Cetin 
said that the proposal concerning the European Stability Pact 
was submitted by the new French Government and was then 
transformed into a joint European Union [EU] initiative. Cetin 
explained that the guiding idea behind this initiative consists 
of resolving the minority and border problems lying at the basis 
of the instabilities in Europe through negotiations. He 
stressed that some of the Central and East European countries 
are still afflicted with minority and border problems. 
  [Begin Cetin recording] One cannot say that the initiative 
was welcomed by the relevant countries. Although this was not 
explicitly stated, these countries are being told the following: 
You have a European perspective, but we do not want you to bring 
your problems into the EU. You must first try to solve these 
problems among yourselves. We are willing to assist you to this 
end, establish a security system, and support you. First and 
foremost, however, you must discuss the minority and border 
problems. Conduct bilateral negotiations and reach agreements, 
or establish regional and multilateral platforms of negotiation. 
[end recording] 
  The foreign minister explained that an opening document will 
be adopted in Paris in connection with this issue. The document 
will outline the initiative's philosophy and its principal 
parameters, Cetin reported. He added that Turkey is ready to 
make every possible constructive contribution to the initiative. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

