<F P=100> INTER-EUROPEAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Belgium's Claes on EU Troika Visit to Algeria </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Belgium's Claes on EU Troika Visit to Algeria </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105084494 Paris Radio France International in French 0630 
GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3105084494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio France International </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] A condemnation of violence and support for 
political dialogue and the economic reforms launched by 
President Zeroual's regime are the results of the brief visit to 
Algiers by the Greek, German, and Belgian troika of European 
Union foreign ministers. After he returned to Brussels last 
night, Belgian Foreign Minister Willy Claes spoke to Quentin 
Dickinson: 
  [Begin Claes recording] It seems clear to me that if Algeria 
does not receive financial and economic aid from the 
international community, it will find it very difficult to 
overcome two challenges simultaneously: terrorism as evolved by 
the fundamentalists on the one hand; and public opinion, which 
in fact is suffering financially and economically from the 
consequences of the policy on structural reform. If we want to 
provide a social safety net, if we want to give a concrete 
signal to the people that something is starting to move and 
changing in the right direction, aid has to come from abroad. 
Otherwise, I really do not see how the Algerian Government can 
make its program successful. [end recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

