<F P=103> AU3105093994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cologne Deutschlandfunk Network </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] NATO Secretary General Woerner has canceled his 
participation in the NATO foreign ministers' meeting, which is 
scheduled next week in Istanbul. In a letter to the 16 member 
states, which was published today, Woerner says that he is 
following his doctors' advice in not attending the meeting. 
After the summer vacations, however, he expects to be able 
fully to resume his responsibilities again. 
  The former FRG defense minister has been suffering from 
cancer of the colon since 1992. 

</TEXT>

