<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security Council To Meet on Kurdish Refugees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Council To Meet on Kurdish Refugees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2705201194 London Kanal-6 Television in Turkish 1600 GMT 
27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2705201194 </F>
<F P=104>  London Kanal-6 Television </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Security Council [NSC] is scheduled to 
meet tomorrow under President Suleyman Demirel. On the agenda 
of the meeting is the [Kurdish] migration from Turkey to 
northern Iraq, and the PKK [Workers Party of Kurdistan] camps in 
Nakhichevan. 
  According to available information, the NSC will discuss the 
situation of those who migrated from some villages of Turkey 
near the Iraqi border into northern Iraq. At present there are 
5,000 people in northern Iraq who came from Turkey. Kanal-6 had 
already reported the PKK's role in bringing about the migration. 
  The NSC will also discuss the PKK camps in Nakhichevan. The 
PKK camps in Nakhichevan have already been tracked down. There 
was talk in Ankara of the possibility of launching a military 
operation against the region where the camps are located. 

</TEXT>

