<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   German Experts To Prepare Closing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    German Experts To Prepare Closing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3005122994 Hamburg DPA in German 1126 GMT 30 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU3005122994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- A group of experts led by Walter 
Hohlefelder, chief of the Department on Reactor Safety in the 
Federal Environment Ministry, left for Ukraine on 30 May to 
prepare steps for closing down the Chernobyl nuclear reactor. 
Two reactor blocs of the power plant are currently still in 
operation, while the third one was closed down following a fire. 
  The experts are primarily developing a concept for gradually 
closing down the whole reactor, setting up a second 
"sarcophagus" for the defective reactor, and ensuring an 
adequate power supply by completing reactor blocs under 
construction at three other sites in Ukraine. 

</TEXT>

