<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Conference on Stability in Europe Convenes in Paris </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Conference on Stability in Europe Convenes in Paris </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Daskalov Meets Counterparts </H4>

<F P=102> AU2705184494 Sofia BTA in English 1819 GMT 27 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2705184494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Paris, May 27 (BTA) -- Bulgarian Foreign Minister 
Stanislav Daskalov, who is attending the Conference on Stability 
in Europe, met with Peter Tarnoff, U.S. Under Secretary for 
Political Affairs, head of the U.S. delegation. The sides 
exchanged views on the need to intensify bilateral political 
contacts. They considered possible ways of expanding 
cooperation between Bulgaria and the Organization for Economic 
Cooperation and Development, of this country's accession to GATT 
in the near future, and international financing of transport 
infrastructure projects that would resolve Bulgaria's 
difficulties arising from sanctions enforcement against Serbia 
and Montenegro. 
  Mr. Daskalov also met with Latvian Foreign Minister Egils 
Levits to discuss prospects for the development of bilateral 
relations. 
  Mr. Daskalov met with G-24 Secretary General Jean-Claude 
Paye 
and the permanent representatives of the G-24 member states. 
The sides went into the prospects for deepening cooperation 
between Bulgaria and G-24 with a view to speeding up Bulgaria's 
reform process. 
  Mr. Daskalov and French Minister for European Affairs Alain 
Lamassoure discussed matters related to Bulgaria's speedier 
integration into the European Union and the prospects of the 
initiative for signing a European stability pact. Matters under 
discussion also included cooperation between Bulgaria and G-24 
and relaxing entry visa requirements between Bulgaria and France. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

